Consider a complete undirected graph with vertex set {0,1,2,3,4}. Entry W<sub>ij</sub> in the matrix W below is the weight of the edge {i, j}
$$$W = \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 8 &amp; 1 &amp; 4  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; {12} &amp; 4 &amp; 9  \cr 
   8 &amp; {12} &amp; 0 &amp; 7 &amp; 3  \cr 
   1 &amp; 4 &amp; 7 &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   4 &amp; 9 &amp; 3 &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$$
What is the minimum possible weight of a spanning tree T in this graph such that vertex 0 is a leaf node in the tree T?

Consider a complete undirected graph with vertex set {0,1,2,3,4}. Entry W<sub>ij</sub> in the matrix W below is the weight of the edge {i, j}
$$$W = \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 8 &amp; 1 &amp; 4  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; {12} &amp; 4 &amp; 9  \cr 
   8 &amp; {12} &amp; 0 &amp; 7 &amp; 3  \cr 
   1 &amp; 4 &amp; 7 &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   4 &amp; 9 &amp; 3 &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$$
What is the minimum possible weight of a path P from vertex 1 to vertex 2 in this graph such that P contains at most 3 edges?
